cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CR 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve authorship attribution. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with classification tasks, which makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper also deals with security and privacy concerns related to authorship attribution, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category.
